"If rice is the cereal supplied, it should be parboiled. # Iodine\nIodine defi ciency is a major specifi c defi ciency that entails serious consequences, and there is no excuse for it in humanitarian assistance. The distribution of iodized salt (30 to 50 mg of iodine per kg of salt) is a highly effective prevention method. Alternatively, iodized oil may be injected (providing protection for at least three years), or administered orally (providing protection for approximately one year). # Summary\nThe above shows that there is no single solution to the supply of essential micro-nutrients in the case of groups that rely exclusively on humanitarian aid."